CHAT.comment: This is a breakfast time meal tape. The youngest brother and the mother seem to do most of the talking. The TC hardly speaks at all. Most of the conversation is disjointed and it is often very difficult to hear what is being said.

u.a: little brother is chanting to himself .
BRO makes little eating noises and hums at the same time .
it is really hard to hear what they are saying much less know what they are talking about
sounds of Bro drinking and swallowing , and then humming and singing for next seventeen seconds .

e.ga: humming to the tune of deck the halls

u.a: annoyed that no one is answering him
difficult to hear this conversation going on in the background .
